by Resilient Acceleration » Fri Jul 23, 2021 12:23 am

I feel like the historical knowledge of people in this site is primarily stronger on WW1, WW2, and the Cold War, meaning that most points of divergence and ideologies of interest came or is dominant from around these times (whether low or high effort). There is thus less content on the historical periods before that, where critical society-building, population spread, and institutional development happens. I think a divergence with a focus on these era can led to a significantly more interesting world of esoteric (but in its context, completely rational) ideologies, history, socio-cultural order, and maps.
